content.text:
The PRESIDING OFFICER. Under the previous order, all postcloture time 
is considered expired.
  The Senator from Mississippi.
content.speaker: The PRESIDING OFFICER

content.text:
Mr. WICKER. Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the votes 
following the first vote in this series be 10 minutes in length.
content.speaker: Mr. WICKER

content.text:
The PRESIDING OFFICER. Is there objection?
  Without objection, it is so ordered.
  The question is, Will the Senate advise and consent to the Zatezalo 
nomination?
content.speaker: The PRESIDING OFFICER

content.text: Mr. WICKER. I ask for the yeas and nays.
content.speaker: Mr. WICKER

content.text:
The PRESIDING OFFICER. Is there a sufficient second?
  There appears to be a sufficient second.
  The clerk will call the roll.
  The senior assistant legislative clerk called the roll.
content.speaker: The PRESIDING OFFICER

content.text:
Mr. DURBIN. I announce that the Senator from New Jersey (Mr. Booker) 
and the Senator from New Jersey (Mr. Menendez) are necessarily absent.
content.speaker: Mr. DURBIN

content.text:
The PRESIDING OFFICER. Are there any other Senators in the Chamber 
desiring to vote?
content.speaker: The PRESIDING OFFICER

content.text:
The result was announced--yeas 52, nays 46, as follows:

                      [Rollcall Vote No. 275 Ex.]
content.speaker: The RECORDER

content.text: The PRESIDING OFFICER. The Senator from Arkansas.
content.speaker: The PRESIDING OFFICER

content.text:
Mr. COTTON. Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that with respect 
to the Zatezalo nomination, the motion to reconsider be considered made 
and laid upon the table and the President be immediately notified of 
the Senate's action.
content.speaker: Mr. COTTON

content.text:
The PRESIDING OFFICER. Without objection, it is so ordered.
  Under the previous order, with respect to the Esper nomination, the 
motion to reconsider is considered made and laid upon the table and the 
President will be immediately notified of the Senate's action.
content.speaker: The PRESIDING OFFICER
